race.comment: CUBAN CIGAR (6) caught the eye first-up at Wyong then made good late ground but was denied again last start over 1200m at the Beaumont track. Lightly raced three-year-old who gets to this trip for the first time which looks perfect. Ready to win. SATNESS (2) hasn't fired since a surprise first-up effort at Rosehill on 8 November. Has an outstanding record here on his home track. Gets in nicely after the 3kg claim so he is certainly worth another chance. IVANA (5) has been freshened up since a poor effort over this course and distance seven weeks ago. Slight query over 1400m off a let-up but definitely has the ability to test these if on-song. CUBAN RAIN (8) came from the clouds but just missed out when resuming over 1010m at Moruya recently. Up in grade but over more ground she should be hard to hold out. AUDENZIA (4) has won two from two this prep, both over today's course and distance. Progressive type who loves it here so must be respected on a seven-day back-up.
